<paragraph blockId="24.[151,448,1837,1863]" box="[151,448,1837,1863]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,448,1837,1863]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[151,448,1837,1863]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,448,1837,1863]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,257,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Lacertus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Garsault" box="[264,448,1837,1863]" pageId="24" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<number box="[389,448,1837,1863]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1764.0">1764</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,1909,2010]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1437,152,479]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="26" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
The spelling 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1788" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1788" box="[307,410,1909,1934]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[307,410,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Lacertus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Garsault" box="[519,1076,1909,1935]" pageId="24" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764" yearSuffix="p">
Garsault (
<number box="[637,701,1909,1935]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1764.0">1764</number>
: pl. 668, 669, 674; table, p. 
<number box="[1037,1068,1909,1935]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="14.0">14</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for his genus accommodating the “Lézards” is distinct from 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[505,787,1946,1972]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[505,596,1947,1972]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Lacerta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" box="[603,787,1946,1972]" pageId="24" pageNumber="42" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Editio decima, reformata. Tomus I. Holmiae, Laurentii Salvii, [i - iv] + 1 - 824." type="book chapter" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[725,787,1946,1972]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It was consistently used by the author in this work and the following ones (
<bibRefCitation author="Garsault" box="[398,576,1984,2010]" pageId="24" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1765) Explication abregee de 719 plantes, tant etrangeres que de nos climats; &amp; de 134 animaux, en 730 planches … suivant l'ordre du livre intitule Matiere Medicale de M. Geoffroy. Paris, i - xvi + 1 - 472." type="journal article" year="1765">
Garsault 
<number box="[512,576,1984,2010]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1765.1767">1765</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Garsault" box="[590,652,1984,2010]" pageId="24" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1767) Description, vertus et usages de sept cents dix-neuf plantes, tant etrangeres que de nos climats; et de cent trente-quatre animaux, en sept cent trente planches … et rangees suivant l'ordre du livre intitule Matiere Medicale de M. Geoffroy. Paris, P. Fr. Didot, i - xvi + 1 - 472 + 1 - 20, pl. 1 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1767">1767</bibRefCitation>
) and therefore cannot be considered as an incorrect subsequent spelling as stated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Welter-Schultes" box="[393,817,152,178]" pageId="25" pageNumber="46" refString="Welter-Schultes, F. W. &amp; Klug, R. (2009) Nomenclatural consequences resulting from the rediscovery of Les figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medicine, a rare work published by Garsault in 1764, in the zoological literature. Bulletin of zoological Nomenclature, 66 (3), 225 - 241." type="journal article" year="2009">
Welter-Schultes &amp; Klug (
<number box="[689,753,152,178]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2009.0">2009</number>
: 
<number box="[764,809,152,178]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="234.0">234</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
or a typographical error. The spelling 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1788" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1788" box="[1264,1367,152,177]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1264,1367,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had a common pre-Linnaean usage and appeared in particular in sources of Garsault that we identified above (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gessner" box="[151,313,226,252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Gessner, C. (1554) Historiae Animalium. Liber II de Quadrupedibus oviparis … Tiguri, Christ. Froschoverum, [i - iv] + 1 - 110." type="book chapter" year="1554">
Gessner 
<number box="[252,313,226,252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1554.1587">1554</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gessner" box="[326,388,226,252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Gessner, C. (1587) Historiae Animalium. Liber V qui est de Serpentium Natura ... Tiguri, Officina Froschoviana, [i - vi] + 1 - 85 + 1 - 11." type="book chapter" year="1587">1587</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schroder" box="[400,575,226,252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="45" refString="Schroder, J. (1672) Pharmacopoeia medico - chymica, sive Thesaurus pharmacologicus … Lugduni Batavorum, Felicem Lopez d'Haro, [i - lxxvii] + 1 - 845 + [846 - 859] + 4 - 33 + [1 - 59]. [Other editions: 1641, 1649, 1656, 1662, 1665, 1680, 1685, 1705]." type="book chapter" year="1672">
Schröder 
<number box="[513,575,226,252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1672.0">1672</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ray" box="[587,704,226,252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="44" refString="Ray, J. (1693) Synopsis methodica animalium quadrupedum et serpentini generis ... Londini, S. Smith &amp; B. Walford, [i - xiv] + 1 - 336." type="book chapter" year="1693">
Ray 
<number box="[641,704,226,252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1693.0">1693</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This spelling was also used by de la Cepède (
<number box="[1256,1316,226,252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1788.0">1788</number>
<emphasis box="[1316,1329,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">c</emphasis>
: 
<number box="[1345,1393,226,252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="447.0">447</number>
), to whom this neonym was previously credited (
<bibRefCitation author="David" box="[673,881,264,290]" pageId="25" pageNumber="37" refString="David, P., Dubois A. &amp; Smith H. M. (2002) A corrective note on the authorship of taxa credited to Lacepede and Bonnaterre in the Introduction to the SSAR's reprint of Shaw's General Zoology, Volume III, Amphibians and Reptiles, with remarks on some of Lacepede's works. Newsletter &amp; Bulletin of the international Society for the History and Bibliography of Herpetology, 3 (2), 16 - 27." type="journal article" year="2002">
David 
<emphasis box="[753,811,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[818,881,264,290]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[891,924,264,290]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="24.0">24</number>
). Following the criteria provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubois" pageId="25" pageNumber="38" refString="Dubois, A. (1987) Again on the nomenclature of frogs. Alytes, 6 (1 - 2), 27 - 55." type="journal article" year="1987">
Dubois (
<number box="[160,226,304,330]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, we consider it as an autoneonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[695,987,304,330]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[695,790,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacerta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" box="[798,987,304,330]" pageId="25" pageNumber="42" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Editio decima, reformata. Tomus I. Holmiae, Laurentii Salvii, [i - iv] + 1 - 824." type="book chapter" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[926,987,304,330]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(family 
<taxonomicName authority="Batsch, 1788" authorityName="Batsch" authorityYear="1788" box="[1094,1410,304,330]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">
<emphasis box="[1094,1241,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">LACERTIDAE</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Batsch" box="[1250,1410,304,330]" pageId="25" pageNumber="36" refString="Batsch, A. J. G. C. (1788) Versuch einer Anleitung, zur Kennniss und Geschichte der Thiere und Mineralien. Erster Theil. Jena, Akademischen Buchhandlung, i - viii + 1 - 528, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1788">
Batsch, 
<number box="[1349,1410,304,330]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1788.0">1788</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<number box="[1410,1418,301,315]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2.0">2</number>
). Therefore, the nominal species 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[553,938,341,367]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="agilis">
<emphasis box="[553,731,342,367]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacerta agilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" box="[740,938,341,367]" pageId="25" pageNumber="42" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Editio decima, reformata. Tomus I. Holmiae, Laurentii Salvii, [i - iv] + 1 - 824." type="book chapter" year="1758">
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[872,938,341,367]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, being the nucleospecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[1299,1397,342,367]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacerta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1299,1397,342,367]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacerta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by subsequent designation of 
<bibRefCitation author="Fitzinger" box="[462,701,378,404]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Fitzinger, L. J. F. J. (1843) Systema Reptilium. Fasciculus primus. Amblyglossae. Vindobonae, Braumuller &amp; Seidel, 1 - 106 + i - ix." type="book chapter" year="1843">
Fitzinger (
<number box="[584,648,378,404]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1843.0">1843</number>
: 
<number box="[659,692,378,404]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="20.0">20</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, is also that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1788" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1788" box="[877,979,379,404]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[877,979,379,404]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,152,479]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<bibRefCitation author="Garsault" box="[198,387,416,442]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault (
<number box="[318,379,416,442]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1764.0">1764</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
illustrated three nominal species, easily identifiable, in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1788" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1788" box="[1210,1313,416,441]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1313,416,441]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1788" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1788" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquatilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus aquatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1788" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1788" box="[268,484,454,479]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="terrestris">
<emphasis box="[268,484,454,479]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus terrestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lacepède, 1788" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1788" box="[541,726,454,479]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[541,726,454,479]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These are discussed successively below.
</paragraph>
